- - - ( PHP & Databses ) - - -


- To connect to a database, you would need 
  an instance of the PDO class 



- ( Example Code 1.1(w/ Explanations) ):

• $dsn = "mysql:
 host=*Your_Host;
 port=*Your_Port;
 dbanme=*Your_DB_name;
 user=*Your_Username;
 charset=*Your_CharSet;
 ";
/*
$dsn ( Data Source Name ), a string that declares
the users connection to the database,e.g..
• host
• port
• database name
• user
• character set
*/


• $pdo = new PDO($dsn);
// Creates the PDO instance


• $statement = $pdo->prepare("select * from posts");
// Preparing a Query Statement that would be Sent 


• $statement->execute();
// A method that sends the query to execute 


• $results = $statement->fetchAll( PDO::FETCH_ASSOC );
// Fetch all of the results made by the sent query
// PDO::FETCH_ASSOC, the method of how the received data will be structured 


• foreach( $results as $data ){
 echo "<li>" . $data['*Key'] . "<li>";
}
// Outputs Received Data



